Time Series Modeling and Forecasting

I am going to study the monthly deaths from Lung Diseases (bronchitis, emphysema and asthma) in the UK, from 1974 to 1979. There are three data sets: 1) ldeaths contains the total monthly deaths, 2) mdeaths has only males monthly deaths and 3) fdeaths has females monthly deaths. Note that ldeaths= fdeaths+ mdeaths.

The goal is to build a model for forecasting the monthly deaths from Lung Diseases in the UK. Steps I considered in my analysis:

I splited each dataset to 2 datasets: i) The Training dataset contains observations from 1974 to 1978 and ii) the Testing dataset has the data of 1979.

I fited a time series model to the training ldeaths data set. Then I ploted the data, ACF, and PACF. Next, I described and discuss the steps I followed. Finally I wrote down the equation of the model.

In order to find an adequate time series model for all the training datasets I first checked for seasonality and trends. Next I checked iid noise. The datasets reveals seasonality and slight downward trend. Thus, I used difference in operartors to eliminate the trend and seasonality. Then, I checked iid again, and stationary. The results showed a stationary data. Finally, I looked for p, q, d, P, D, Q appropiate indicators using the ACF, and PACF graphics to come up with the more adequate model comparing AICs.
